properties.abstract: From Linthal, via the traffic-free mountain village of Braunwald with its alpine huts scattered across the sun-drenched slopes, the route goes up to Oberblegi Lake at the foot of the Glärnisch. The legendary lake with no visible outlet is one of the most attractive mountain lakes in Switzerland.
properties.description:
From the starting point in Linthal, the route begins straight away with a steep surfaced road that goes up to Brulaui. You reach the highest point of the route with a strenuous ride along the gravel road up to an altitude of 1,599 metres. A steep descent runs down to the Nussbüel mountain restaurant. From Nüssbüel to Braunwald, the trail leads through sparse forests, past old farmhouses, with a view of Ortstock and Tödi.

Through the scattered village of Braunwald, you climb to the legendary Oberblegi Lake, which is surrounded by steep rock faces. You can quench your thirst on the way to the Bächialp, and also try a piece of fresh alpine cheese. From Oberblegi Lake, you can enjoy a rapid descent on the steep but well-maintained alpine road. With a constant view of the bottom of the valley, you go past scattered alpine huts, and through forests and meadows to Schwanden.
